stem was considered and rejected: behavior does not require real external network/OS/subprocess; local test DB is sufficient to catch real persistence bugs. Agentic/Workflow rejected because this behavior validates storage integrity, not model output quality.","test_description":"Use real repository layer against local test DB. Execute a conversation path including at least one regeneration, then query persisted records and assert all turns exist (user, first draft, regenerated draft/final) with expected linkage and monotonic timestamps.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Integration with real DB adapter is needed to catch schema/ORM/transaction mapping failures.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.83,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is a multi-step agentic sequence: initial generation -> tone decision -> regeneration -> final output selection. Per MULTI-STEP and integration-brake(d), orchestration/state handoff across LLM-involved stages should be Workflow. Integration was rejected because stubbing all model decisions can miss real sequencing/handoff failures when live calls and asynchronous returns interact. Agentic alone was rejected because the requirement is specifically about end-to-end replacement across multiple steps, not one model decision.","test_description":"Run end-to-end with real model calls on prompts that reliably trigger tone regeneration. Capture customer-visible response channel and internal artifacts; assert only regenerated response is returned to user while rejected draft is retained only in internal logs/audit. Repeat across runs to catch non-deterministic sequencing bugs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test explicitly exercises multiple real agentic steps and final visibility contract, matching Workflow boundary.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.19,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.17,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
